## Full-Text Search

FTS5 is built into SQLite. Search chunks via `KnowledgeGraph::search_chunks_fts`:

```rust
// Returns Vec<(ChunkId, ObjectId, content_text)> ordered by relevance rank
let results = graph.search_chunks_fts("psychohistory", 10)?;

for (chunk_id, obj_id, content) in results {
    if let Some(obj) = graph.get_object(obj_id)? {
        println!("{}: {}", obj.name, content);
    }
}
```

FTS5 query syntax supports: phrase (`"hari seldon"`), prefix (`found*`), boolean
(`empire AND foundation`), and column filters. See SQLite FTS5 docs for full syntax.

**The `chunks_fts` virtual table is kept in sync automatically** by three DML
triggers defined in `SQL_SCHEMA` in `storage.rs`. Never manually INSERT into
`chunks_fts` — always go through `upsert_chunk`.

