## Async Patterns

### Correct: fully async HTTP provider (no thread blocking)
```rust
async fn embed(&self, text: &str) -> Result<Vec<f32>> {
    let resp = self.client.post(&url).json(&body).send().await?.json().await?;
    Ok(parse_embedding(resp)?)
}
```

### When wrapping sync work in async context
Use `tokio::task::spawn_blocking` — do not call blocking code directly in an async fn:

```rust
let text = text.to_string();
let result = tokio::task::spawn_blocking(move || {
    // CPU-bound or blocking sync work here
    do_sync_work(&text)
}).await??;
```

**Anti-pattern removed (was BUG-5):**
```rust
// ❌ DON'T — locks a std::sync::Mutex inside an async fn, blocking the Tokio thread
async fn embed(&self, text: &str) -> Result<Vec<f32>> {
    let model = self.model.lock().unwrap();  // blocks executor thread!
    model.embed(vec![text], None)
}
```

